@startuml 01-key-derivation
title Key Derivation Flow (Master KEK)

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam roundcorner 10
skinparam shadowing false

skinparam activity {
    BackgroundColor #E3F2FD
    BorderColor #1976D2
}

|User|
start
:Enter Master Password;
note right
    User provides password
    as Uint8Array (not String)
    for memory hygiene
end note

|Extension|
:Load Application Pepper;
note right
    High-entropy secret
    baked into extension build
    (defense-in-depth)
end note
note right
    it adds friction but isn't truly secret in open source
end note

:Combine Password + Pepper;
:SHA-256(Password + Pepper);
note right
    Pre-hash before PBKDF2
    to include pepper in derivation
end note

:Load Salt from IndexedDB;
note right
    32 bytes random
    Generated during Genesis
    Stored unencrypted
end note

|WebCrypto API|
:PBKDF2-HMAC-SHA256;
note right
    **Parameters:**
    - Iterations: 600,000
    - Salt: 32 bytes
    - Output: 256 bits
end note

:Master KEK (256-bit);
note right
    Key Encryption Key
    Used to wrap/unwrap
    Device Private Keys
end note

|Extension|
:secureWipe(passwordBuffer);
note right
    **Critical:**
    passwordBuffer.fill(0)
    Immediately after use
end note

stop

legend right
    | Symbol | Meaning |
    | KEK | Key Encryption Key |
    | PBKDF2 | Password-Based KDF 2 |
    | AES-KW | AES Key Wrap (RFC 3394) |
endlegend

@enduml
